The paper discusses the use of deep learning methods for human activity recognition, which falls under the category of machine learning and computer vision. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) are likely sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of LSTM networks, which are a type of neural network, indicating that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses the potential for real-life applications, suggesting that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also a possible sub-category.
